The paper deals with error-correcting codes, specifically separable binary Goppa codes, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CC) communities. The paper also discusses the minimal distance of these codes, which is a key metric in cryptography (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents a chain of embedded codes, which is a technique commonly used in signal processing (cs.SI).
